### ===== REAL-WORLD SCENARIOS =====

### Complete user flow: Register -> Upload Avatar -> Search -> Play
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser_phase6",
  "email": "testuser_phase6@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!",
  "display_name": "Test User Phase 6"
}

### Then login to get token
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser_phase6@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

### Use token from login response in subsequent requests
### Upload profile picture
POST http://localhost:3000/api/upload/avatar
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-files/profile.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Search for music
GET http://localhost:3000/api/search?q=favorite+song&limit=10

### Start playback
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/me/player/play
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN

{
  "track_id": "TRACK_ID_FROM_SEARCH",
  "context_type": "search",
  "context_id": "favorite+song"
}

